cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with synthesizing images from text descriptions. It also involves learning disentangled representations of content and style, which is a common topic in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses adversarial training, which is a popular technique in both the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on several image datasets, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
